On 25.3.1884 the part in Sussex became part 
    of the parish of Wisborough Green, so that thereafter Alfold was wholly in Surrey. 
    See also Table 2, notes (a), (d) and (h).

That part which until 1.4.1933 formed parts of the parishes of 
    Shalford and Witley. See also Table 2, note (h).

That part which until 1.4.1933 formed parts of the parishes of 
    Shalford and St. Martha. See also Table 2, note (h).

That part which until 1.4.1933 formed part of the parish of 
    Elstead. See also Table 2, note (h).

That part which until 1894 formed part of the parish of Shalford. See 
    also Table 2, note (e).

That part which until 1.4.1933 formed part of the parish of 
    Elstead. See also Table 2, note (h).
